he code working while preserving the structure for the upcoming mapping step.\n\n## Implementation Details\nReplace the interface:\n```typescript\ninterface Input {\n    startUrls: Array<{ url: string; tag?: string }>;\n    maxRequestsPerCrawl: number;\n}\n```\nReplace the call:\n```typescript\n// Temporarily pass only URLs; mapping with labels will be added in next step.\nconst urls = input.startUrls.map(item => item.url);\nawait crawler.run(urls);\n```\nIf validation is desired:\n```typescript\nfor (const item of input.startUrls) {\n    if (!item.url) {\n        log.warning('Missing url in startUrl entry', { item });\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling and Edge Cases\n- If `url` is missing, the crawler will receive an undefined string, which may cause runtime errors. The validation loop above warns and could skip invalid entries.\n- The `tag` field is optional; if absent, the default handler will be used later (after mapping step).\n- The `maxRequestsPerCrawl` field remains unchanged.\n\n## Validation\n- TypeScript compilation passes without errors: `npm run build` (or `npx tsc --noEmit`).\n- Existing unit tests (test/main.test.ts) still pass; they do not depend on Input interface.\n- Manual test: run the actor locally with the new input format (e.g., via `echo '{\"startUrls\":[{\"url\":\"https://apify.com\"}],\"maxRequestsPerCrawl\":100}' | npm start`). The crawler should start and scrape the default page.\n\n## Dependencies and Inputs\n- Requires step `update-input-schema` to be completed, so the new input schema is in place (though the actor can still be tested with direct JSON input).\n- The next step `map-input-to-requests` will replace the temporary URL extraction with a proper mapping to Request[] with labels.\n\n## Constraints\n- Do not change the core scraping logic or router yet.\n- Maintain backward compatibility for the test file (test/main.test.ts does not use Input interface).\n\nThis is the ONLY task you must complete in this iteration. Do not work on other steps.",
